We first note that the “Fixed Assets” account is initialized by the “Initial20231231001” row with an amount of 5,000,000.00. In the subsequent transactions the only item that affects the fixed assets is the depreciation entry (Depreciation20240101001), for which the amount is 45,751.67. (In accounting the net value of fixed assets is computed as the initial balance plus any additions less accumulated depreciation.)

Thus, the net fixed assets “end value” is calculated as follows:

  Fixed assets net End Value = 5,000,000.00 – 45,751.67 = 4,954,248.33

Therefore, we have:

  Fixed assets net Initial Value = 5,000,000.00
  Fixed assets net End Value = 4,954,248.33
